  "Question": "<p>A fair coin is flipped repeatedly until it turns up tails five times. What is the expected number of heads before that happens?</p> <p>Based on the link given in the comment, I have found it can be solved using the recursion <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_600\"><math alttext=\"E(n)=\\frac{1}{2}(E(n)+1)+\\frac{1}{2}(E(n-1))\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>E</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>E</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>E</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> which is equivalent to <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_601\"><math alttext=\"E(n)=E(n-1)+1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>E</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>E</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span>. Is it correct?</p>",
  "Title": "Expected number of heads before it turns up tails five times",
  "Tags": "probability,expected-value"
}